BRANQUARBranquar is the easiest way of implementing automatic bank switching in the Acorn Atom. If the Atom Basic Interpreter encounters a statement that is not in the standard roms then it handles over the control to branquar. This software will search each `toolbox at #Axxx for the statement. If it is not there, then an error 94 will occur. Besides searching for statements, Branquar also tracks the operating system vectors at #200 if they point to an address at #Axxx.Branquar used to have several internal statements as well, but due to space issues there are only two left in the AtoMMC version:`ROM     select and lock rom`UNLOCK  unlock rom